The paper discusses the challenges of concurrent programming and the need for automated verification and synthesis techniques. It specifically focuses on distributed synthesis in the setting of Mazurkiewicz traces, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of reactive programming models like Erlang and Scala, which are programming languages (cs.PL). The discussion of formal analysis and automata-based verification suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the mention of regular languages and finite-state automata suggests a connection to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
